observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to validate and send confirmation letters to various creditors to confirm or determine the exact amount of liability of the LGU;
b. Ensure that complete supporting documents are attached to various claims before recording of the liability account;
c. Reverse the entry made for those claims that were not pushed through for some reason, such as cancellation of transaction or non-submission of complete documents, if any; and
d. Exert efforts to locate the documents relative to the long-outstanding payable and make the necessary adjusting entries, if there are any.

We recommended that the Management:
a. Instruct the Property Officer to conduct an inspection immediately upon delivery of the products and prepare an Acceptance and Inspection Report;
b. Verify and check whether the goods delivered are in accordance with the purchase order specification and inform the supplier immediately of the noted defects;
c. Deduct a liquidated damage in case of breach;
d. Submit the insurance policy for medical equipment installed in the mobile clinic; and
e. Justify as to the reason why the mobile clinic was in the custody of the supplier.

We recommended that Management:
a. direct the Municipal Accountant to immediately submit the unsubmitted vouchers for the month of December 2024 together with their complete supporting documents;
b. require the Municipal Accountant to strictly observe the submission of the financial reports within the prescribed periods in the subsequent years, to afford the Audit Team with the opportunity to conduct a timely and objective examination of the financial reports and related transactions of the LGU;
c. consider augmenting the workforce at the Office of the Municipal Accountant, to ensure prompt recording and processing of transactions, and the ultimate delivery of the necessary reports; and
d. consider the use of E-NGAS and E-BUDGET systems, which are readily available and offered by the Commission on Audit, to facilitate the accounting and budgeting transactions of the Municipality and the timely submission of the financial statements and other related reports.

