We recommended that the Management:
Direct the General Services Officer to maintain individual property cards for all PPE owned by the LGU;
Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain a complete PPELC to ensure proper monitoring of PPE;
Provide the documents required in the disposal procedures as specified in COA Circular 89-296; and
Abide with the prescribed rules and procedures specified in COA Circular 2020-006 in the conduct of the one-time cleansing of PPE and provide the supporting documents related to the adjustments made to the financial statement balances.

We recommended that the Management:

Enforce existing laws, ordinances as well as the provisions of the LGU’s ecological solid waste management plan specifically in the storage and segregation of wastes;

Construct the fence in the vicinity according to the facility’s detailed plan;

Repair and utilize the available equipment for recycling purposes to prevent accumulation of too much waste, if possible; and

Continue to mobilize the active participation of the residents and barangay officials by informing, educating, monitoring, and assisting institutions and households in their proper waste disposal more so the residual wastes.

We recommended that the Management: 

Require the Municipal Engineer to prepare and submit a valid and consistent information, particularly on the questionable dates written in the documents as discussed in this AOM;

Issue a written notice and demand letter to the Contractor for immediate repair and rectification of identified defects;

Instruct the Municipal Accounting Office to check the veracity of all documents before processing claims;

Justify the deficiencies noted above; and

Adhere to the prescribed provisions and guidelines mentioned in the 2016 Revised Implementing Rules and Regulations of RA No. 9184.

We recommended that the Management: 

Formulate and follow a detailed and well-defined written policy and guidelines in hiring Job Order Workers, Contract of Service, and consultants;

Attach to the payrolls  a Certification from LCE that the work to be performed is not performed by the regular/permanent employees;

Submit the perfected contracts within five working days upon approval, together with the supporting documents for review and evaluation process.

